h requirements), we show that the dynamic\nprogramming algorithm can be modified to output the minimum congestion\nembedding in time $O(k^2n)$.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 16 Feb 2012 20:03:44 GMT"}],"update_date":"2012-02-17"}
